stimulus:
Pattern Separation Task

You are about to start a new task. In this task, you will be asked to view a series of common objects and remember them for a later memory test. While you view each item, please answer yes or no to the following questions:

Will the object fit inside a lady’s medium shoe box?
Can you carry the object across the room using only your right hand?

Before we begin the actual task, let’s try a few practice trials.

Press the space bar to continue

Pattern Separation Task

In the practice trials, you will see 4 items twice. Please answer the question presented underneath the item by pressing "y" for "yes" or "n" for "no" as well as trying to remember them for a later memory test.

Press the space bar to continue

Pattern Separation Task

You will be tested on your memory for the objects you saw earlier. Please indicate whether each item is 1 = definitely old, 2 = maybe old, 3 = maybe new, or 4 = definitely new. “Definitely old” means you are confident that you saw the object. “Maybe old” means that you think you saw the object, but not completely sure.   ”Maybe new” means that you don’t think you saw the object, but not completely sure. “Definitely new” means you are confident that you did not see the object.

Press the space bar to continue

Pattern Separation Task

We will begin the actual task. You will see 30 items. Please answer the question presented underneath the item as well as trying to remember them for a later memory test. Please note that the memory test will be given 30 minutes after this viewing session.

Press the space bar to continue
